    <stitle>CAB: 5000i AND 9000i CONVENTIONAL - REMOVE - Remove WINDSHIELD WIPER ARM AND BLADE ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="x1602108" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Remove WINDSHIELD WIPER ARM AND BLADE ASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1602181">Figure 81</hotlnk>
            for Items in parentheses.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Unlatch fiberglass tilt hood on both sides and raise hood to full open position. On 5000
                <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                series with a Butterfly Hood, unlatch both latches on right and/or left side hood and raise hood as
                required.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove windshield washer hoses (Items 1 and 2) from driver and/or passenger side windshield
                wiper arm and blade assemblies (Item 3).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove driver side and/or passenger side windshield wiper arm and blade assemblies (Item 3)
                by pulling windshield wiper arm slide lever (Item 4) out at the spline and pull windshield wiper arm and
                blade assembly off the spline.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1602181" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602192.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="472px"/>
            <caption>Figure 81. Windshield Wiper Arm/Blade</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. WINDSHIELD WASHER HOSE (DRIVER WIPER ARM)</callout1>
                <callout1>2. WINDSHIELD WASHER HOSE (PASSENGER WIPER ARM)</callout1>
                <callout1>3. WINDSHIELD WIPER ARM AND BLADE ASSEMBLY (DRIVER AND PASSENGER)</callout1>
                <callout1>4. WINDSHIELD WIPER ARM SLIDE LEVER</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
